text: Nana Yaa, better known by her stage name Nayaah, is a Ghanaian Gospel singer and songwriter based in Luton, United Kingdom. ==Early life== She began singing when she was 10 years old in Accra, Ghana and has toured Ghana and Nigeria extensively. ==Awards and nominations== {| class="wikitable" !Year !Event !Prize !Recipient / Nominated work !Result !Ref |- |2017 | rowspan="2" |Africa Gospel Awards |Artists of excellence Europe | rowspan="5" |Herself | | |- | rowspan="2" |2015 |Discovery Artiste of the Year | | |- |Praisetek Gospel Music Awards |Outstanding Praise and Worship Leader | | |- |rowspan="2"|2014 |Prosperity Gospel Awards |Female Gospel Artiste of the Year | | |- |Prestigious Africa Gospel Awards |Discovery of the Year | | |} ==Discography== ===Albums=== {| class="wikitable" !Year !Title !Production credit !Ref |- |2013 |God is not a man |Kwame Keys (Echoed Music) | |} ===Singles=== {| class="wikitable" !Year !Title !Production credit !Ref |- |2017 |Pillar | rowspan="4" |Kwame Keys (Echoed Music) | |- |2015 |You're Great | |- | rowspan="2" |2014 |Worship Medley | |- |God | |} ==References== ==External links== *Official Facebook Page Category:Living people Category:Musicians from Accra Category:Ghanaian female singers Category:Gospel singers Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:People from Luton
